If you like to gamble, I tell you I'm you're man,
You win some, lose some it's all the same to me,

The Ace Of Spades.

Playing for the high one, dancing with the devil,
Going with the flow, it's all the same to me,
Seven or eleven, snake eyes watching you,
Double up or quit, double take or split,
The Ace Of Spades.

caption.text:
.
.  Closer

No you won't see me every work break 
And in every space between your 8 week shift
I have turned into your favorite pages of your favourite book
Which you read in your bed
Which you hug with the sound of your laughter
And which your fingers still lingers
After you've fallen asleep reading me

If that would make me closer to you
I will turn myself into your favorite book
And i will hug you with every pages you turned
And i will embrace you in the arms of words
As if you're the only thing i could hold

Don't be too sad when the sun part 
Leaving the sky too bright with the color of tequila
It's just me saying something you can understand
The light reflected from your vest
Everytime i poke from behind
And i become the color of the wind
Walking you home with the wet coal under your soles
For i become the pillow in your bunk
I'll never let you hit the bed 
without my hand behind your head

You've been here
You'll be here every morning
These words will stay here
To be remembered and forgotten
So come back here next morning
I'll make these prose even familiar to you 
Than all the routine you've been through
If this would make me closer to you

So tell me which one is stronger,
The sky or my eyes?
Here goes my interminable months filling the absence of your touch

caption.text: Takut luber pipinya

Girl;

You walk like life is fine,
You smiles like nothing's gonna hurt you,
And damn,
Your laugh is the crunchiest thing ever
But i can see you through

You didn't even say hi when we met
You showed all shoulder and back
Without a smile
While i know you were dying inside
Because when you laid your eyes into mine,
It broke me how you missed me
You can try play it cool girl,
But i know all you want is me sitting next to you
Talking and blabbering for hours 
But i can't
I just can't
Because i am not that kind of man
And i am not sorry
Though i wish i could,
But here,
I confess i may have a little crush on you
You are one of a kind in my life
But i don't think this is the right time
Or maybe you could just give me some time

Boy;

I knew you knew how much i long for the time we would meet
Yet when you sat there i gave no words nor warm hugs,
I try to play it cool but you knew it killed me,
Because when i laid my eyes into yours
Didn't it breaks you how much i miss you?
You knew how i want to be close but it's impossible
Maybe there's not much left for us
Maybe there's nothing happened from the first time
You always take it casually while i always take it personally
From day to day till you away
Words has been shared and spoken,
Yet i am still clueless as ever.
Maybe we're just not right
Maybe if we could buy us some time to make it right

Early October,
Andre Harihandoyo's Mr. Time
Endless drizzles
Vast murky open sky
Lighthouse,
The scent of your car
Cold gushing 2 pm wind
Wet converses
Coldplay's sky full of stars 
Same old red parka,
The glitter in your eyes
Your smile met mine
As we had hot coffee midnight
And you slept two blocks away from me
And i couldn't sleep
Thinking how we could be
And i could't stop pretending
That it wasn't just anything
So i put the blanket on you
Cause i got enough warmth
From watching you sleep and sound

And i remember we climbed that hill
We hiked a mountain
In the same rainy day
When i couldn't take it no more but you lift my carrier,
As i turned around and you said,
"Let me bring your bag will you? I need to break some sweat in this cold rainy day"
When it was fog all around and you let me lead the path,
Sweet thin mist between your iris and mine, 
I wait to reveal the mysterious sign behind those eyes
As you always giving me faith,
And you let me be the first to see the first ray of December sun
Light breeze on the back of my nape,
Your damn sweet voice behind my ears

And you let me adjust your matress,
you told me how to choose my own path around the bushes,
As we joked about who's going to murder who first, and make it looked like an accident

You know what's the problem here?
You always did it casually but i always took it personally

We're starting as a team in need but something happened inside me

Now i'm having cold coffee at cold days
With none others but strangers
I talked about him when the image of you talking to me with mountain scenery on my reverie,
Yes i finally able to let go,
But that's kind of a little bullshit
Because you will forever have me,
And i couldn't being objective
I bet you realize it
Though i always say no
And never say so
I will forever choose you

caption.text:
Today's weather just like you yah,
Cold, damp, crisp, 
Just the one that i love the most,

Today's weather talks everything about you,
Drizzles used to be my favourite type,
Until i decide i won't let my eyes got teary like today's rainfall

And the rain,
Always bring the colours of you
And the ambience of the moment, once upon i fall in love with you

I wish i could tell
And scream to the vast open sky,
To the gleamy murky sky 
that resemblance your eyes, 
and to the pisces truss
As i clutched my heart,
I pray this pain will last

So i could face tomorrow's fate with open mind, 
And decide whether to smile or give you a bare sight

Yes you kind of get on my nerves sometimes,
But to hate you,
That'll be the last thing i plead

I wish i have that kind of patient,
To wait for the right time to tell you how much you affects my life
And not to be feverishly trying to sending all of my love at once
But it's so hard to hold back,
When the feeling inside is about to explode at any given time

caption.text:
I let go of you not because i don't love you anymore,
I let go of you because the world needs you more than i do
I let you slide out of my grip because society miss you more than i do

But shit with that,

What the world knows about me and you?

Nor even our hearts could recognize each other anymore
Even our name feels sour in our mouth

So what's the matter?

What matter is

Because i let go of you
Because i felt your hand brush my fringers then i felt no more
Because i couldn't grasp you
Because i couldn't stop you from walking away

Because i let go of you

Because i know i have to

caption.text:
And we walked in crescendo
In rainy days without jacket
And i lost count in your pace,
Though i knew it's because your feet are longer than mine, 
And your steps are wider than mine
You were walking beside me, 
In front of me,
Then you ran without me.. But i knew you didn't run to leave me,
You ran so you could get your jacket for me, with that i wouldn't wet from rain for too long

And you ran in crescendo
With your pale blue converse
And all i see was your shoes, fading away when you leave,
And all i see was your worn out converse when you ran to me,
As you do it in crescendo

#poem #converse #shoes #drawing #art -for the boy who didn't even know i draw his converse
